text: Manaria is a genus of sea snails, marine gastropod mollusks in the family Buccinidae, the true whelks. ==Species== Species within the genus Manaria include: * Manaria brevicaudata (Schepman, 1911) * Manaria burkeae Garcia, 2008 * Manaria canetae (Clench & Aguayo, 1944) * Manaria chinoi Fraussen, 2005 * Manaria clandestina Bouchet & Waren, 1986 * Manaria formosa Bouchet & Waren, 1986 * Manaria fusiformis (Clench & Aguayo, 1941) * Manaria galatheae (Powell, 1958) * Manaria kuroharai Azuma, 1960 * Manaria lirata Azuma, 1960 * Manaria makassarensis Bouchet & Waren, 1986 * Manaria thurstoni Smith, 1906 ; synonym * Manaria insularis Okutani, 1986: synonym of Chryseofusus chrysodomoides (Schepman, 1911) ==References== Category:Buccinidae
title: Manaria (gastropod)
